Durban - A 31-year-old suspect is due to appear in the Verulam Magistrate's Court today charged with the murder of alleged thief who was doused with petrol and set alight in Parkgate, Verulam. KZN police spokespersonÂ Colonel Thembeka Mbele said the suspect was arrested on Friday and is due to appear in court today. According to Prem Balram, director of Reaction Unit SA, the victim was accused of stealing a grass cutter on Thursday. Balram said when they attended the scene, the man sustained burns to 90 percent of his body. "Members of Reaction Unit South Africa were called out to a property off Tottenham Road at approximately 11:12 pm after the critically injured man collapsed on the driveway. "The caller confirmed that the individual had suffered extensive burns to more than 90% of his body. "Upon arrival the man confirmed that he had a stolen a grass cutting machine from contractors who were working on the roadside in Parkgate." Police arrested the supervisor of the grass cutting business after he attempted to report a case of theft of equipment at the Verulam SAPS today.